<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-22T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-22T15:00:00-05:00" n="312" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.76/71: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-22T15:00:00-05:00">January 22, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6. Reference your 16, January 20, 3 p.m. Department approves your action
                            in declining to ask the authorities of the British Concession to
                            withdraw their objection to the proposed installation.</p>
                        <p>Repeat to the Embassy at Peiping and Hankow and to the Consulate General
                            at Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>